Azure Storage is Microsoft’s online service to store different types of data safely in the cloud. It is:
   -------------- Benefits of Azure Storage---------------
Reliable and secure – your data stays safe and available.
Scalable – it can handle small to very large amounts of data.
Accessible globally – you can access your data from anywhere using the internet.
Developer-friendly – supports many programming languages like .NET, Java, Python, etc.
Easy to manage – you can use tools like Azure Portal, Azure CLI, PowerShell, or Azure Storage Explorer to manage your data.
In short: Azure Storage helps store and manage data online, securely and from anywhere.

First Create a azure Account every service using or creating through azure account.

There are 4 most important azure storage services .
1.Blob storage 
2.File Storage
3.Table Storage
4.Queue Storage
